                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> <br />What I have seen. I am a 60 necro from TZ. Leveling up I read the same posted topic a long time ago. I went out to find out for myself what worked for me.<br /><br />What I found to be true for me is. <br />1 using fear on undead (solo spectre in ferrott) I did this for weeks while leveling there. I would take my cha down to 9, if I remember correctly (I know it was a single diget number)Fear would very rarely break and my pets did more damage and less mana used.<br /><br />I Would then get my cha up over 50 think in the 64 range. Still along time ago but know it was in the 50+ pretty much during this time. Fear would break more offten my pet would have to fight alot and I used more mana. Which would make me not ready for next 6 min pop. Cause I had to med. : ) <br /><br />This was only for fear it seemed that lower cha made the fear last longer. But that was me not trying to tell you what to do. <br /><br />Charm. Charm in lower guk High cha, low cha seem to be a random time and nither was that good breaking randomly and lasting for about 5 min on a good one. Thank god for FD. So I dont think that charsma has much to do with undead charm spell just luck of the draw.<br /><br />But its an easy test see what works for you. I know necros that used charm to level very well in lower guk but wasnt for me I hated closed confined areas and loved the outdoors to do my fearing. <br /><br />Plus I have a friend that I work with plays a necro, he found the same thing lower cha seems to help his fear, but nothing with charm no matter what his charsma is.<br /><br />Try it out yourself, but for me I run around with very low charsma now : )<br /><br />TytenTZ 60 DE Warlock</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
